<br>
DO use shields: <br>
<br>
There's no way we will do enough damage to keep aggro, and to have one less hand swinging for a proc, the amount of FD and evade to be used by monk/rogue will increase considerable.  Decreasing damage to the mob and increasing the # of CH's per mob.  Increasing the time to kill the mob, and increasing the percentage of failure.<br>
<br>
Don't use shields: <br>
<br>
The 3 Minute warrior is easily replaced by the an SK or pally.  The amount of damage they take will be less than ours b/c we aren't using a shield.  Descreasing the number of seconds in the CH chain.  Also, warriors dual wielding have an increased chance of ripiste, therefore increasing the amount of damage taken, and decreasing the CH timer again.  Also warriors don't get 1 handed 28/30 weapons the way SK's and pallys do, we're at a big disadvantage there.  A SK can keep aggro without ever hitting the attack button.  The same might be true with a pally, though I've never heard about it.  <br>
<br>
I think a block mod on the shields is a good idea, despite my above statements.  I do think warriors need something to compensate for them not being able to effectively use them.  <br>
<br>
Again dual wield is supposed to be a benefit, it does less damage than 2handers now, and if they add procs and block mods to the shields, it will basically be useless.  There needs to be a min damage or damage modifier to the offhand.  <br>
<br>
It's been 2 expansions now without any real upgrades, it's about time.<br>
<br>
This is the same argument I've posted again and again.  I'm ready to start cutting and pasting it now, LOL.<br>
