The work involved to attain it is not out of line. Yes there are better weapons. Also there are better armor drops than the velius armor quests. Everything has a flow to it. A steady progression to it. It seems to me poeple want to &quot;jump&quot; right into the &quot;top of the line modules&quot;. It just rearly works that way. Item upgrads are slow and hard work. I use my epics in grind groups and raids all the time. Yes i have better than epics. I choose my epics or combination of epic and another weapon about 75% of the time. I rearly have taunt issues and i am very happy with the epics. I would like to point out that the differants in a lvl 51 and a lvl 60 is huge! Now we have AA points. Well the same goes for that also. A lvl 60 no AA vs a lvl 60 with 20 AA is huge again. In the end its all about the gear. Yes there are ubar monks with 4.5k unbuffed hp but, in that same ubar guild sits a warrior with 6k unbuffed hp. Just cant compare a 3 year old lvl 60 warrior to a 1 year old lvl 60 warrior. It would be sad if the 3 year old charecter can be beat out by a 1 year old warrior. When i got my epics it was a great upgrade for me. Sure primal is better but my epic was achivable at the time and i needed better gear to adventure into ST for a primal. Its just like i said, &quot;There is a flow to things&quot;.<br>
Well thats about it for my thoughts on it for now.<br>
<br>
Gydeen 60 warlord<br>
